Counterfeit goods and narcotics are not incredibly dense, heavy, metallic, radioactive elements. They aren't easily picked up by Xrays, metal detectors, and radiation checks. Try sticking Pu up your anus and walking through a metal detector if you don't believe me.<br>
<br>
People get through customs by using false documents. You could give false documents purporting Uranium to be Ice Cream but the security checks are going to disagree with the paperwork.<br>
Anything metal shows up as blue on X ray screens. Guns and knives are clearly visible. This technology could be further fine tuned to identify and distinguish between  heavier elements and regular steel. <br>
<br>
I agree with X. <br>
