<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  BUT the other side of the equation is where the pay-off comes, non-proliferation (which the US is a leader)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The US owns the largest stockpiles of fissile material in the World. Also the largest number of defensive nuclear warheads. Its easy to preach to others about developing nukes when you own most of them. Other nations see this hypocrisy for what it is. An attempt to keep them out of the nuclear club. Like India and Pakistan some will ignore the demands of Big Brother. Others seeing this will also defy it. Those without nukes and not wanting to rely on the US for protection will choose between constructing nukes or buying them. Proliferation has only been slowed by the expense of programs. Not stopped. It can never be stopped.<br>
